{{Infobox video game | title = When Two Worlds War | platforms = PC | released = 1993 | genre = Strategy |image = When Two Worlds War cover.jpg |caption = |alt = |publisher = Impression Games |developer = Impression Games }} '''''When Two Worlds War''''' is a 1993 video game by Impression Games. It is a strategic simulation of interplanetary conflict.
== Critical reception == Amiga Format thought the game was neither simplistic nor shallow.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/Amiga_Format_Issue_054_1993_Future_Publishing_GB_christmas_edition|title=Amiga Format - Issue 054 (1993)(Future Publishing)(GB)[christmas edition]|date=1993}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080517120826/http://amigareviews.classicgaming.gamespy.com/whentwow.htm|title=Amiga Reviews: When two worlds war|date=2008-05-17|access-date=2018-02-23}}</ref> Meanwhile, CU Amiga Magazine felt the game was identical to [[Utopia (video game)|Utopia]] in every way, sans the fun.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/cuamiga-magazine-046|title=CU Amiga Magazine Issue 046|date=December 1993}}</ref>
